-- MOVES-Sterne Agee boosts investment banking unit with three hires
-- 
-- Tue Aug 26, 2014 02:28PM EDT
-- None



Aug 26 (Reuters) - Financial services firm Sterne Agee said it hired three managing directors in its investment banking division.

James Murray joins as an investment banker in the financial institutions group from investment banking firm Freeman & Co.  Sterne Agee named Jeffrey D. Jones as Midwest head of depository investment banking. Jones spent 11 years in the investment banking group at Sandler O' Neill & Partners LP and three years in the investment banking group at Lehman Brothers.  The company appointed Matthew Clark as a managing director in equity research focusing on community and regional banks on the West Coast. Clark held similar positions at Credit Suisse, Keefe, Bruyette and Woods and Deutsche Bank Securities.